President Barack Obama announced his intention to appoint Mark Feierstein as Deputy Administrator for Latin America and the Caribbean at USAID, and Osvaldo Gratacós as Inspector General at the Export-Import Bank of the United States. Feierstein is currently a senior partner and vice president at Greenberg Quinlan Rosner, where he has conducted public opinion research in over 30 countries. He has previously worked at USAID and the Department of State, and has experience in negotiating with diplomats from the Americas on regional issues. Gratacós is currently serving as the Acting Inspector General at the Export-Import Bank, and has previously worked as a legal advisor for Motorola and the USAID Inspector General's Office. He has also taught international business transactions at the University of Virginia. Gratacós holds degrees from the University Interamericana de Puerto Rico, the University of Massachusetts, and the University of Florida.